-- Kremlin says rouble fall largely caused by emotions, speculative mood - RIA 
-- By Maria Kiselyova
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 09:40AM EST
-- None



MOSCOW, Dec 16 (Reuters) - The fall in the rouble is driven largely by emotions and a speculative mood, RIA news agency quoted Dmitry Peskov, a spokesman for President Vladimir Putin, as saying on Tuesday.

